“Tailors have played a significant role in the growth of Siyaram’s since the beginning. We hope to improve their lifestyle by training them with the necessary skills”, says Mr. Ramesh Poddar on World Tailors Day.

Karigars or tailors are an integral part of India and have served as the backbone of the textile community since the very beginning. Despite their significant contribution, Siyaram’s recognized a gap in the community - the acknowledgement, recognition and upliftment they need to grow professionally. 

To bridge this gap, we introduced the "Tailors Training Programme" to equip them with all the necessary skills of national and international level tailors so that they can elevate their fabrics into masterpieces effortlessly. 

Since its inception, the tailors training program has been gaining popularity and positive feedback from all corners. Let's hear from our CMD during his recent interviews with different prominent radio channels about the same. 

#siyarams #comehometosiyarams #karigar #karigars #tailor #tailoring

On the occasion of World Tailor’s Day, Siyaram’s kickstarted the "Tailors Training Programme" to appreciate and give back to the community of thousands of tailors in India. We conducted free upskilling workshops and sessions for tailors in different cities, to help them gain formal training in upgrading their skills for consistency.

At our programme, our tailors were trained in formal ways of taking measurements, drafting patterns, staying updated on the developments in the fashion industry and the garment trade, and having the know-how to benefit their customers with the change in the processes they are applying in their day-to-day business. 

This Tailors Training Programme is a conscious effort to bring Siyaram’s vision to life - bridge the gap between the tailoring community and their customers. Most tailors in India miss out on gaining the opportunity to have a formal education. However, we wanted to change the narrative and ensure a bright, successful future for tailors today and in the future by upskilling them. 

Transforming the lives of over 1500 tailors, we hope to continue this initiative and impact 50,00+ tailors going ahead. We thank all of our tailors, our community and customers for supporting us at every way to make our karigars lives better and happier.

#siyarams #comehometosiyarams #karigar #karigars #tailor #tailoring
